&lt;p&gt;The Office of the Chief Dental Officer - England is seeking to appoint 1 x 1.0 WTE SES Project Manager (Band 7) on a fixed term contract ending 31 March 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that the reason for the fixed term of your contract is this is a short-term pilot project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a SES Project Manager, the post holder will work as part of a dynamic team in delivering the Oral Health Improvement in Special Educational Settings (SES) project. This project will be led by the Office of the Chief Dental Officer, and is part of NHS England &amp; NHS Improvement’s broader Children &amp; Young People Learning Disabilities &amp; Autism Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project is dynamic, complex and inextricably linked to many aspects of health and social care and is ambitious in its aims. This requires a significant cultural change within the existing dental workforce, support for clinical disciplines and public engagement as it strives to improve the oral health and overall wellbeing of children and young people being cared for in residential special schools in England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will need to be able to commence working from 04 January 2021, subject to all successful recruitment checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
